  <discussion>Symphyotrichum ×amethystinum is the F1 hybrid between S. ericoides and S.
        novae-angliae, encountered sometimes throughout the area where the two parental species
        co-occur. It is morphologically intermediate; it has non-spiny, sparsely stipitate-glandular
        phyllaries and rose-violet rays in mid-sized heads. Forma leucerythros Bemis and forma
        leucos Bemis have been described within this hybrid and may represent recombinants or normal
        population color variants.</discussion>
